sub_title: EY EMEIA ServiceNow Alliance Team | ServiceNow Practice Head (FSO) at EY, The Netherlands | ServiceNow Certified Master Architect (CMA)
summary:
I am a Senior Manager in the Digital and Emerging Technology group within the EMEIA Financial Services (FSO) Technology Consulting practice of EY Advisory Netherlands LLP.

I lead ServiceNow practice at EY, The Netherlands, and also part EY EMEIA ServiceNow alliance group which makes me responsible for enabling and accelerating ServiceNow business in 12+ large markets in EMEIA.

I am also responsible for a few global roles under EY-ServiceNow alliance, just to name few – I am Founder and Global domain owner for the ServiceNow Badges program, Global ServiceNow’s ATP (Authorized Training Program) Lead, etc.

In my ServiceNow alliance role in The Netherlands, my responsibilities include alliance contracts, financial tracking & analysis, go-to-market sales plans, engagement support, relationship development, ServiceNow Talent strategy, Capability growth, delivering value to clients and business plans, etc.

I am ServiceNow Certified Master Architect (CMA) [EMEA, 2020 COHORT] The CMA program is the pinnacle of ServiceNow certification, I am proudly part of the CMA elite group of individuals spearheading successful ServiceNow programs around the world, making the work … Flow!

ServiceNow Techno-Functional Implementation Capabilities:
- ESG
- ITSM Suite
- SPM
- Service Portal
- CSM
- SecOps 
- GRC/IRM 
- Data Privacy
- Operational Resilience 
- Vendor Risk Management (TPRM)
- HR Service Management
- Custom Applications (Crazy about it)

I am passionate about training & enabling people (~1K resources trained)

Devoted to achieving the goals of every project/program/initiative I work on. Taking a customer’s idea or a new product and breaking that into end-to-end, smaller, doable pieces of work, never losing sight of the big picture and final outcome excites me and keeps me on my toes. 

Adaptable to the needs of the project, customer, and my team. And change do not scare me. I could say I'm self-motivated and hard-working. 

What you should know about me is that I take my profession seriously. I work endlessly on every single project or program and will do what it takes to achieve all the objectives if there are stumbling blocks, I learn from them, adapt, change, and better myself and then move forward until the moment I can celebrate a successful project or program.

I am a single, born Indian, Dutch national. Living in Europe for 6 Years. I was born in Lucknow – known for its delicious food, lucid language, and traditional clothing.

Besides ServiceNow and Digital Transformation, I also have a passion for cooking food, photography, and Numismatics.

awards.title: Recognition for Delivering positive ServiceNow Outcomes.
awards.description:
Through Recognition & Awards channel at Accenture, I received recognition from Lolita L. Moser. 
This award is worth 1000 recognition points with a beautiful message from Accenture's Journey to Cloud (J2C) Leadership Team (ServiceNow Global Team) stating -

"As a high-growth team we are continuously transforming the way we operate. To improve and advance our ability to deliver the best ServiceNow services available. You have continued, daily, to meet this challenge and have truly set a standard of excellence. It is our team, and efforts like yours, that all of our success has been built from. In recognition of your efforts, our Cloud leadership has found an extra way to say “thank you for all of your hard-work, commitment to clients and contribution."

profile_positions.description:
Responsible for our alliance with ServiceNow at The Netherlands. 

The EY-ServiceNow Alliance is a dynamic, driving force. 
Together we are changing the way the world works by enabling better experiences and evolving how business gets done. 

The EY and ServiceNow Alliance combines ingenuity with a leading digital workflow platform. We innovate together to deliver workflow automation that enables better connectivity across systems, drives greater resource efficiency and delivers seamless human-centric processes.
We remove bottlenecks to provide easy-to-consume information when and where it’s needed, delivering frictionless experiences for both customers and employees. Harnessing technology to power human enterprise. 
With our deep industry expertise, we fuse our business acumen and collaborative mindset with the versatility of the ServiceNow platform to drive innovation, performance and growth.

profile_positions.description:
The ServiceNow Certified Master Architect is the highest achievement in the ServiceNow training and certification catalogue or pinnacle of ServiceNow certifications. 

A certified master architect is seen as a thought leader who shares best practices and can lead enterprise customers through the most complex and demanding ServiceNow implementations. The Master Architect is a trusted technical advisor and a valued partner on the digital transformation journey with ServiceNow. 

They are skilled in guiding customers with technology strategy and governance as well as actual solution design and architecture. Their best-practices guidance supports customers across technical planning and execution activities—from building the right technology strategy and implementation plan to designing the platform governance process and operating model.
